# AdaptiveAIContent — Build Guide

These components reduce the maintenance burden of FAQ and Troubleshooting sections. When platform behaviour changes, Kapa retrieves updated context from live docs automatically at runtime. Gemini responses for general troubleshooting are pre-generated at build time — no runtime function, no latency, no loading spinner. The `fallback` prop ensures every entry degrades gracefully if AI is unavailable.

## Response Generation by Mode

| Mode            | When         | How |
|-----------------|--------------|-----|
| `docs`          | Runtime      | `window.Kapa` JS bridge with 8s timeout, falling back to `kapa_proxy.mts` if the JS bridge is unavailable |
| `general`       | Build time   | Gemini via `generate-troubleshoot-responses.mjs`, stored in `generated-responses.json` |
| `fallback-only` | Always       | Static `fallback` prop — no AI call made |

