## File Structure

```
src/components/AdaptiveAIContent/
├── index.ts
├── FAQ.tsx                         # collapsible details/summary, runtime Kapa
├── Troubleshoot.tsx                # collapsible details/summary, build-time JSON or runtime Kapa
├── useAIResponse.ts                # sessionStorage cache + eager fetch hook
├── api.ts                          # window.Kapa JS bridge (8s timeout) + kapa_proxy fallback
├── generated-responses.json        # build-time Gemini output (gitignored; script seeds `{}` before build/start)
└── styles.module.scss
scripts/
└── generate-troubleshoot-responses.mjs
netlify/functions/
└── kapa_proxy.mts
```

**Kapa approach:** `api.ts` exposes `fetchFromKapa` (JS bridge, 8s timeout) and `fetchFromKapaProxy` (REST proxy). `useAIResponse.ts` uses `fetchFromKapa` by default. If the bridge proves unsupported, swap the single call in `useAIResponse.ts` to `fetchFromKapaProxy` — no component changes needed.

**Performance:** `useAIResponse` reads `sessionStorage` synchronously on first render — cached responses are instant with no loading state. On a cache miss it fetches eagerly on mount. `docusaurus.config.ts` has `preconnect`/`dns-prefetch` for both Kapa endpoints.

