## Loading State — Progress Bar

While `loading || completing`, render:
```jsx
<div className={styles.progressWrap}>
  <div className={styles.progressTrack}>
    <div className={`${styles.progressFill}${completing ? ` ${styles.progressComplete}` : ''}`} />
  </div>
  <span className={styles.progressLabel}>
    Fetching the most relevant and up-to-date information from our docs…
  </span>
</div>
```

`completing` is a local state in each component — set `true` when `!loading && response && !error`, cleared after 260ms via `setTimeout`. This plays `kapa-finish` (88%→100%) before revealing content.

SCSS keyframes: `kapa-progress` (9s, `cubic-bezier(0.12, 0.08, 0.02, 1)`, fills to 90%) and `kapa-finish` (0.25s, `from 88% to 100%`, override with `!important`).

